Four Crew Members Died in First Air Crash, Nunatsiaq News Says

-- B y   C h r i s   F o u r n i e r
-- 
2011-08-21T16:33:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/four-crew-members-died-in-first-air-crash-nunatsiaq-news-says.html
The four crew members of a First Air
Boeing 737 plane that crashed in the Canadian Arctic yesterday
were among the 12 fatalities, Nunatsiaq News  reported .  First Air isn’t releasing names of the dead or details
about passengers, Nunatsiaq News, based in Iqaluit, Nunavut,
said on its Web site, citing a statement by  Chris Ferris , First
Air’s vice president of marketing and sales. Ferris, who spoke
to reporters at the company’s office in Kanata, near Ottawa,
said the cause of the accident isn’t known, Nunatsiaq News said.  First Air said yesterday 12 people were killed in the crash
near Resolute Bay, about 2,100 miles northwest of  Montreal .
Three survivors are in stable condition the  Royal Canadian
Mounted Police  said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Fournier in Toronto at 
